[node name="RichTextLabel" type="RichTextLabel" parent="MarginContainer/VBoxContainer" unique_id=333452876]
layout_mode = 2
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "You were once 
beautiful, fragrant, young.
With auburn hair
afraid of snakes
until He, deity of the sea
Enraptured by lust
pursued you to your refuge
the temple of Athena.

Everything was taken
White dress stained red
Athena’s curse
You still fear your slithering, hissing hair

Now people flee from
You monster, not woman
Look, a singing bird,
a handful of dusty gravel
spatters down.

He
Perfect man, Greek god
Revered upon by millions
Yet the [b]masses[/b] are ignorant, [b]innocent[/b].
Though he shall be terrified,
For [b]he[/b] and his servants soon shall be [b]petrified[/b].
"
fit_content = true
horizontal_alignment = 1

